  "text": "significant allelic biases in gene expression in each group were detected using edgeR and corrected for multiple testing via the BenjaminiHochberg method [CITATION_1] (Figure 1 ). To increase robustness of our significance calls, genes were only considered for allelic analysis if the sum of their allele-specific read counts was .1 CPM in all six profiled TSC lines. Under this CPM cutoff, 13,593 genes were eligible for allelic expression analysis (Supporting Information, Table S1 ).",
